  <T n="name">0x80F63507<!--Mentoring--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Skill_Mentoring_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:58db05324cf750d4</T>
      <T n="text">0x4B29C5A2<!--<b><font color='#199C2C'>Mentoring</font></b> allows skilled Sims to pass on their knowledge to other Sims. Once they reach <b><font color='#199C2C'>level 5</font></b> in a Mentorable Skill, they can Mentor other Sims in that Skill (as long as the Mentor's Skill is a higher level than the Mentee's), which speeds up Skill gain.\n\nTo find out if a Skill is Mentorable, you can check its description in the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Skills panel</font></b>. Here you can also learn on which objects Mentoring is available.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Skill_Mentoring_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:58db05324cf750d7</T>
      <T n="text">0xF628AE08<!--Mentoring can be offered or asked for in two different ways. When a Sim is <b><font color='#199C2C'>already practicing a Skill</font></b>, the Mentor can select the Offer Mentoring interaction on them, or the Mentee can select Ask for Mentoring on the Mentor.\n\nYou can also select an Offer Mentoring or Ask for Mentoring interaction on a <b><font color='#199C2C'>Skill-building object</font></b>. If accepted, this will make the Mentee start practising the Skill before Mentoring starts. Handy, huh?\n\nMentoring is free by default, but Mentors can <b><font color='#199C2C'>Offer Paid Mentoring</font></b> on Skill-building objects to Sims from other households. Ka-ching!--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Skill_Mentoring_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:58db05324cf750d6</T>
      <T n="text">0x8E692A1D<!--When a Sim receives Mentoring, this speeds up the rate of their Skill gain. The biggest impact on the speed is the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Mentor's Skill level</font></b>â€”a Sim at Skill level 10 will be better at Mentoring than a Sim at Skill level 5!\n\nThere are other ways to boost Mentoring. For example, a Mentor can buy the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Super Mentor</font></b> Reward Trait from the Rewards Store.--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
